A TEXAS mum reported her son to cops after he told her he’d sexually assaulted one of their neighbours. According to the New York Post, the 29-year-old was arrested and charged with sexual assault and burglary in San Antonio on Friday, 11 June. In April, he allegedly broke into the home of a 68-year-old neighbour and sexually assaulted her. ALSO READ | HOSPITAL
HORROR: Patients sleep on the floor The mother’s statement allowed cops to seek a judge’s permission for a cheek swab. The DNA was then compared with evidence cops found at the crime scene, where a match was made. After the results came back, cops pounced to arrest the man.